Analysis: The stress test failed with `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace`. This confirms a leak of class loaders. 

Looking at `ThreadCache.java`:
```java
    WorkerHandle cursorFor(TimelineLedger ledger) {
        TimelineFrame frame = ledger.current();
        if (cursor == null) {
            cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        if (!cursor.matches(frame)) {
            cursor = new WorkerHandle(frame);
            return cursor;
        }

        return cursor;
    }
```
When `!cursor.matches(frame)`, a new `WorkerHandle` is created and assigned to `cursor`, but the old `cursor` is never closed! `WorkerHandle.close()` calls `frame.unpin()`. If `unpin()` is not called, the `TimelineFrame` (and thus the class loader) will never be considered 'drained' and will stay in the `shadow` queue of `TimelineLedger`, preventing the class loader from being garbage collected.

Also, `TimelineFrame.java` and `LoadedGeneration.java` should be checked to see how they handle pinning and class loading.
Plan: 1. Check `src/main/java/io/harbor/textd/core/TimelineFrame.java` and `src/main/java/io/harbor/textd/core/LoadedGeneration.java`.
2. Fix the leak in `ThreadCache.java` by closing the old `cursor` before creating a new one.
3. Verify if there are other places where `WorkerHandle` or `TimelineFrame` are not properly closed/unpinned.

